<http://identifiers.org/uniprot/Q13526>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_527  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1 Pin1 protein is present in the PSD fraction derived from cortical tissues of human brain.\nLiteral: \"Pin1 proteins exist in detergent-resistant dendritic rafts and PSD fractions\"\n\nFig. 2 Pin1 protein, in cortical neurons partially colocalyze with NR1 and Shank3 proteins\"\nLiteral: \"Pin1 proteins also partly colocalized with NR1 proteins along with Shank3 proteins at the dendritic spines of excitatory neuron\". Experimental description: Synaptosome, Dendritic Raft, and PSD Preparation are prepared from **human samples**\nLiteral from M&M: \"Synaptosomes were prepared from frontal cortical tissues of\nhuman brains\"\n\nExperiment of neuronal colture staining are made in **mouse**\nLiteral from M&M: \"Cortical neurons of C57/BL6 mice at E18 and Pin1 knockout mice at P0 were cultured on coverslips for immunocytochemical analysis\"\n\n17/5/2017 Pim\n- I agreed with annotation to human species since fractionation data has the highest resolution and is additionally supported by IF in mouse." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_527" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

